<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7319> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7319" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Leg., envoy 85. Sent by Sulla to talk with Fimbria when he requested a colloquy (App. Mith. 60). This envoy, identified by Münzer (RE 34) and Lintott (Historia 20, 1971, 700 note 22), with the aged consular exile, P. Rutilius Rufus (34), was probably a younger officer, and may have been P. Rutilius Nudus (Badian, Gnomon 33, 1961, 492; cf. H. Bennett, Cinna and His Times 56-57, note 99). On Nudus, see below." .
